Thanks Leon.<br />  I ended up checking the CHR and a connection to one of the CHR pins was bad. One of the traces near a CHR hole was damaged.  I couldnt see the damage, but the multi-meter showed I was not getting a connection so I used a conductive pen and resolved it.<br /><br />Al<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=772">albailey</a> — Wed May 30, 2007 6:22 am</p><hr />
