<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3371&amp;p=24290#p24290"><![CDATA[
Bleeding most time is due to bad connection.  Are the pins clean? Are you sure you didn't cut a trace by mistake when removing the ROMs?  Are you sure the EPROM data is good? (use CopyNES to dump cart and do a bit for bit compare to verify).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=104">leonk</a> — Thu May 17, 2007 11:02 am</p><hr />
